# Core Standards

- Use path aliases (`@app`, `@features`, `@lib`, `@components`, `@pages`) — never `../` from routes, pages, app, or layout.
- Keep `routes/` and `pages/` thin: wire UI only, no business logic.
- Put domain logic in `src/features/<feature>/` with colocated api, atoms, hooks, and components.
- Export feature public APIs from `src/features/<feature>/index.ts`.
- Run `pnpm validate` before opening a PR. ESLint uses `--max-warnings 0`.
- Never use `any`, `enum`, or type assertions (`as Type`). Prefer Effect Schema + `typeof Schema.Type`.
- `as const` is allowed (const assertions); type assertions like `as Foo` are not.
- Never duplicate types that can be inferred from schemas or `as const` + `satisfies`.
- Stack: Effect (Schema + Effects + Atom) + TanStack (Router + Query). Do not introduce Zod or Zustand.
- Follow `no-shortcuts.mdc`: no bypasses (`@ts-ignore`, `eslint-disable`, skipped tests); finish work 100% or ask — never leave tech debt.
- Do not change `eslint.config.js` or `tsconfig*.json` to dodge errors unless the user explicitly asks.

